export const QUESTIONS = {"office_professional":[[{"phase":"situation","question":"How many workstations and endpoints are you running right now across your office?","goodResponse":"Got it — that's a meaningful footprint. Let me ask a bit more about how you're managing all of that day-to-day.","badResponse":"Okay, cool. Well, we handle setups like that all the time.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"When someone's laptop goes down or a remote access issue hits mid-deadline, who's handling that — do you have internal IT, or is it whoever knows the most?","goodResponse":"That's a really common pressure point for firms your size. Relying on whoever's available usually means billable hours stop while the problem gets figured out. Tell me more about how often that happens.","badResponse":"Yeah, we get a lot of calls like that. We can fix those things pretty fast.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a paralegal can't access the document management system during a filing deadline, what does that actually cost the firm — in time, in client risk, in partner headache?","goodResponse":"Exactly — and that's the kind of invisible cost most firms don't quantify until it's already happened twice. That's precisely the exposure we help eliminate.","badResponse":"Yeah, downtime is bad. We can minimize it.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If you had a dedicated IT partner monitoring your systems 24/7 — catching issues before they take someone offline — what would that peace of mind actually be worth to your practice?","goodResponse":"That's the conversation I want to have. Let me walk you through exactly how we'd structure that for a firm like yours.","badResponse":"We have a package that covers all of that.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"Are your attorneys and staff accessing client files through an on-premise server, a cloud platform like SharePoint or NetDocs, or something in between?","goodResponse":"Interesting — a lot of firms are in that hybrid middle ground right now. It tells me something about where your current pain points probably live.","badResponse":"Okay, we support all of those setups.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Have you had any incidents with phishing emails or unauthorized access attempts in the last year — even ones that didn't become a full breach?","goodResponse":"That's worth paying attention to — most firms that eventually get hit had near-misses they dismissed beforehand. What's your current email filtering setup like?","badResponse":"We have security tools that handle that.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If client data were exposed due to a security gap — even an accidental one — what's the realistic exposure for the firm from a bar complaint or malpractice standpoint?","goodResponse":"Right, and that's where the liability calculus changes completely. The cost of prevention is a rounding error compared to that scenario.","badResponse":"That would be bad, yes. We help prevent that.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If we handled your endpoint security, email filtering, and compliance monitoring under one managed service agreement, how much time do you think your senior staff would get back each month?","goodResponse":"That's meaningful time. And that's exactly the shift our clients describe after the first 90 days. Let's talk about what that looks like for your setup.","badResponse":"We can cover all of that for you.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"How are you currently handling backups for client files and case data — is that automated, or does someone need to remember to run it?","goodResponse":"Manual backup processes are one of the first things that slip when people get busy. That tells me a lot about where your risk might be sitting right now.","badResponse":"We can set up automated backups for you.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Has anyone ever had to reconstruct work because a file was lost, corrupted, or saved over — even a small incident?","goodResponse":"Even small reconstruction events are signals of a deeper gap in data integrity. How much time did that cost and did it affect a client relationship at all?","badResponse":"Data loss is a pain. We back everything up.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If you experienced a ransomware event or a server failure and had no verified clean backup, what does your continuity plan look like — and have you actually tested it?","goodResponse":"That's the hard question most firms haven't fully answered. The firms that test their recovery plan are the ones that survive those events intact.","badResponse":"You'd want to have a backup. We can help with that.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your data was backed up automatically every hour with a tested recovery process behind it, how would that change how you think about disaster risk at this firm?","goodResponse":"That mental shift — from hoping to knowing — is what our clients describe as the biggest value. Let me show you what that system looks like.","badResponse":"That's what we offer. Want a quote?","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}]],"tech_company":[[{"phase":"situation","question":"Do you have dedicated internal IT staff, or is infrastructure management handled by your engineering team alongside their product work?","goodResponse":"That's a pretty common setup at your stage — engineers wear a lot of hats. It helps me understand where the gaps usually show up.","badResponse":"A lot of companies do it that way. We can supplement.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"When your engineering team gets pulled into IT issues — network problems, access provisioning, device setup for new hires — how much product velocity do you think that's costing you?","goodResponse":"That's a real distraction tax. The best dev teams I've seen are ruthless about protecting engineering hours — what would it mean if none of those interruptions landed on them?","badResponse":"Yeah, distractions hurt productivity. We handle that stuff.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a key engineer spends even three to four hours a week on IT overhead instead of shipping, what does that add up to over a quarter — especially right before a launch?","goodResponse":"Right — that's a full sprint's worth of engineering time lost to IT admin. And that math usually gets worse as you scale headcount.","badResponse":"It adds up. We can take that off their plate.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your engineering team never had to touch an IT ticket again — fully handled, SLA-backed — what could they ship in that reclaimed time?","goodResponse":"That's the pitch I'd make to your CTO. Let's talk about what a lightweight managed IT layer looks like for a team your size.","badResponse":"We can do that. Want to set up a call?","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"How are you handling device management and security policy enforcement for remote or hybrid team members — MDM solution, honor system, or something else?","goodResponse":"That tells me a lot. A lot of fast-growing teams hit a compliance wall when they go to close enterprise deals and their MDM story isn't clean.","badResponse":"We support all major MDM platforms.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Have you had a security questionnaire from a potential enterprise customer come back with flags around endpoint policy, access control, or SOC 2 readiness?","goodResponse":"That's a dealbreaker scenario that catches a lot of companies off guard. What did that process look like, and did it slow down the contract timeline?","badResponse":"SOC 2 prep is something we help with.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If an enterprise prospect walks away because your security posture doesn't meet their vendor requirements, what does a lost deal like that actually cost — and how many of those could you afford?","goodResponse":"That's the number most founders don't want to say out loud. But it's exactly the number that justifies getting this right proactively.","badResponse":"Losing deals is costly. We can help you get compliant.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If we helped you get your endpoint management and access control policies audit-ready, how many enterprise doors does that open for your sales team?","goodResponse":"That's the ROI story I want to help you tell internally. Let me walk you through how we've done this with other SaaS companies at your stage.","badResponse":"We do compliance prep. Let's get you set up.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"How are you managing user onboarding and offboarding right now — access provisioning, license assignment, equipment setup — when headcount changes?","goodResponse":"Onboarding and offboarding are where security gaps live at growing companies. What does that process look like end to end right now?","badResponse":"We can automate that whole process for you.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"When someone leaves, how confident are you that all their access — SaaS tools, cloud infrastructure, shared credentials — gets revoked quickly and completely?","goodResponse":"That hesitation is telling. Stale access from departed employees is one of the most common root causes of data exposure events we see.","badResponse":"Offboarding gaps are risky. We tighten that up.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a former employee still had access to a production environment or customer data repository — intentionally or not — what's the potential blast radius there?","goodResponse":"That's a scenario that turns into a headline fast. The companies that build access hygiene into the offboarding workflow from day one are the ones that never have to find out.","badResponse":"It could be bad. We handle access management.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If every employee transition — hire or departure — triggered an automated checklist that closed every access door within an hour, how would that change your risk profile?","goodResponse":"That peace of mind is exactly what we deliver. Let me show you what that automated workflow looks like for a team your size.","badResponse":"We can automate that. Want a demo?","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}]],"healthcare":[[{"phase":"situation","question":"How are patient records and clinical data currently stored — are you on an EHR platform, local servers, or a mix of both?","goodResponse":"That hybrid setup is where a lot of practices end up, and it creates some interesting challenges around HIPAA technical safeguards. Tell me more about who manages the infrastructure side.","badResponse":"We work with all the major EHR platforms.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Has your practice ever had to pause operations or delay patient care because a workstation, the network, or the EHR system went down at the wrong moment?","goodResponse":"That's a patient safety and revenue issue at the same time. How long was the outage, and what did that look like from a scheduling and billing standpoint?","badResponse":"Downtime is bad in healthcare. We reduce that.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a HIPAA audit found that your technical safeguards — encryption, audit logs, access controls — weren't fully documented, what does that exposure look like for the practice?","goodResponse":"Right — HIPAA fines scale by volume of affected records, and the documentation burden is the part most practices underestimate. That's exactly where we help close the gap.","badResponse":"HIPAA penalties are serious. We help with compliance.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If you had a managed IT partner that maintained your HIPAA technical safeguards, monitored your systems continuously, and gave you an audit-ready report at any time — how would that change your relationship with compliance stress?","goodResponse":"That's what we hear from every healthcare client we bring on. Let me show you what that documentation package looks like in practice.","badResponse":"We offer HIPAA-focused managed IT. Let's talk.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"How many devices are connected to your clinical network right now — including things like imaging equipment, check-in kiosks, or connected medical devices?","goodResponse":"Medical IoT is one of the hardest things to secure because those devices often can't be patched the same way workstations can. That gives me a clearer picture of the network exposure.","badResponse":"We can audit and secure your full device inventory.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Do you have any visibility into what's happening on your network at any given moment — unusual traffic, unauthorized devices, or access attempts outside business hours?","goodResponse":"Most practices are flying blind on this, and it's not because they don't care — it's because no one's been given the job to watch. What does your current monitoring setup look like?","badResponse":"We provide 24/7 network monitoring.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"Healthcare practices are the number-one ransomware target right now — if an attack locked down your scheduling and clinical systems, what's your realistic recovery timeline?","goodResponse":"Most practices we talk to don't have a tested answer to that. And the practices that get hit find out their recovery plan was theoretical, not operational.","badResponse":"Ransomware is a real threat. We have solutions for that.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If we could get your practice to a point where a ransomware event meant a four-hour recovery instead of a four-week nightmare, what would that be worth to your patients and your revenue?","goodResponse":"That's the math we help practices run. The investment in resilience is always smaller than the cost of the event. Let me walk you through our healthcare-specific package.","badResponse":"We can get you there. Want to schedule an assessment?","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"When a new provider joins your practice, how long does it typically take to get them fully set up — EHR access, email, VPN, workstation — before they can see their first patient?","goodResponse":"That onboarding lag has a direct revenue cost in healthcare. It tells me something about how your IT processes are structured — or whether they've been formally structured at all.","badResponse":"We streamline onboarding for healthcare teams.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Have you had providers or staff frustrated by slow systems, dropped connections, or having to use workarounds to access what they need during patient care?","goodResponse":"Workarounds in clinical settings are where errors happen and where staff burnout starts. What are the workarounds you've seen people rely on most?","badResponse":"We fix performance issues and eliminate those workarounds.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If your clinical staff is spending even ten minutes per shift fighting with slow systems or access issues, what does that add up to across your provider count — and how does that affect patient throughput?","goodResponse":"That's usually tens of thousands of dollars in lost productivity annually when you run the math. And that's before you account for the morale effect on retention.","badResponse":"That time adds up. We fix the root cause.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If every provider at your practice had a reliably fast, secure, always-available workstation experience from day one — what would that do for staff satisfaction and your capacity to see more patients?","goodResponse":"That's the environment we build. Let me show you what our clinical workflow optimization looks like for a practice your size.","badResponse":"That's what we deliver. Let's get started.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}]],"retail_food":[[{"phase":"situation","question":"How many POS terminals are you running, and are they all on the same network as your back-office systems?","goodResponse":"Network segmentation between POS and back-office is one of the first things PCI DSS auditors look at. That setup tells me a lot about where your compliance exposure might be.","badResponse":"We handle POS network setups all the time.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Have you ever had a POS system freeze or go offline during a rush — and had to handle transactions manually or turn customers away?","goodResponse":"That's a revenue and reputation hit in the moment, but it also signals a reliability issue that can come back at the worst times. How often does something like that happen?","badResponse":"We minimize POS downtime with managed IT support.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If your payment system was down for two hours on a Friday night, what does that cost you — in direct sales, in the customer experience, and in the social review risk?","goodResponse":"That's real money, and the Yelp hit can last longer than the outage. Most operators don't budget for that risk until after it happens.","badResponse":"Downtime is costly. We prevent it.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your POS, network, and back-office systems were proactively monitored and a technician was dispatched before you even noticed a problem, how would that change how you run the floor?","goodResponse":"That's the confidence level we aim for. Let me show you what proactive POS monitoring looks like for a business your size.","badResponse":"We provide that monitoring. Want to know more?","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"Are you offering guest WiFi to customers, and if so, is it separated from the network your business systems run on?","goodResponse":"Guest WiFi on the same network as your payment systems is a PCI red flag and a real security risk. Let me understand the full network setup a bit better.","badResponse":"We can set up proper network segmentation for you.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Have you ever dealt with a credit card processing issue — declined transactions, processor connectivity errors, or a chargeback spike — that you couldn't quickly diagnose?","goodResponse":"Those processor issues often trace back to network configuration problems. What did that experience look like from a customer-facing standpoint?","badResponse":"We troubleshoot payment system issues regularly.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a customer's card data was compromised through your network — even indirectly — what does a PCI DSS violation look like for a business your volume?","goodResponse":"The fines, the forensic audit costs, and the brand damage together are usually enough to close a small location. That's why the segmentation and compliance work is so important.","badResponse":"PCI violations are serious. We help you stay compliant.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If I could show you a setup where your guest WiFi, POS network, and back-office were all properly segmented and you had a PCI compliance report ready to go — how much simpler does that make your life?","goodResponse":"That simplicity is worth a lot when an auditor walks in. Let me walk you through what that implementation looks like.","badResponse":"We set that up. It's pretty straightforward.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"Do you have security cameras on-site, and are they connected to your business network or on a separate system?","goodResponse":"Camera systems on the same network as operations are another common attack surface. But more practically — who manages that footage and the storage system behind it?","badResponse":"We handle camera and network integration for retail locations.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"When something goes wrong — a register discrepancy, a theft incident, a vendor dispute — how quickly can you pull up relevant camera footage or system logs?","goodResponse":"If the answer is 'it takes a while' or 'we have to call the camera guy,' that's a gap that costs you in those moments. What does that process look like right now?","badResponse":"We integrate camera and IT systems for faster access.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If you couldn't produce camera footage in time for an insurance claim or a police report after an incident, what does that mean for your coverage and your ability to recover losses?","goodResponse":"That's a gap that turns a solvable problem into an unrecoverable one. Having reliable, accessible footage is as much a business continuity tool as it is a security one.","badResponse":"Footage access matters for claims. We solve that.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your cameras, network, and back-office systems were all managed and accessible from one dashboard — accessible from your phone — how much more in control would you feel running this location?","goodResponse":"That control is exactly what operators tell us they were missing. Let me show you how that unified setup works.","badResponse":"We can build that for you. Let's talk specs.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}]],"trades_contractor":[[{"phase":"situation","question":"How are your field crews currently handling job documentation — photos, work orders, completion sign-offs — is that paper-based, an app, or something in between?","goodResponse":"A lot of trades companies are in that transition phase between paper and digital. It tells me something about where your operational bottlenecks probably are right now.","badResponse":"We help trades companies go fully digital.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Do your crews ever have connectivity issues on job sites that prevent them from pulling up plans, submitting updates, or reaching dispatch reliably?","goodResponse":"That connectivity gap is where delays and miscommunications start. What does a bad connectivity day look like in terms of how it affects the job or the customer relationship?","badResponse":"We have field connectivity solutions for that.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a miscommunication between the field and the office causes a job to get scoped wrong or a change order to get missed, what does that cost you — in rework, in margin, in customer friction?","goodResponse":"That's a margin killer that compounds over time. The best-run trades companies have eliminated that gap entirely with connected field systems.","badResponse":"Miscommunications are costly. We eliminate them.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If every crew member had a reliable device, a connected workflow app, and real-time sync to the office — how much cleaner would your job closeouts be?","goodResponse":"Clean closeouts mean faster billing and fewer disputes. That's the operational outcome we're aiming for. Let me walk you through what that looks like.","badResponse":"We can build that workflow for you.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"How many office staff do you have handling estimating, dispatch, and billing — and are they all working off the same systems?","goodResponse":"When multiple people are working off different versions of data, errors and delays are usually the result. What does your current software stack look like for those functions?","badResponse":"We integrate those office systems for you.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Has your team ever sent a crew to the wrong address, double-booked a job, or invoiced a customer incorrectly because of a scheduling or data entry mix-up?","goodResponse":"Those errors are usually symptoms of disconnected systems, not careless people. How often does something like that happen in a busy week?","badResponse":"We eliminate those data entry errors with better systems.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"When a customer gets a wrong invoice or a crew shows up at the wrong time, what does the follow-up look like — and how does that affect your review scores and repeat business?","goodResponse":"One bad experience gets posted online faster than a hundred good ones get mentioned. That operational reliability directly impacts your reputation and referral pipeline.","badResponse":"Customer experience matters. We help protect it.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your scheduling, dispatch, invoicing, and CRM were all connected and talking to each other in real time — what would you stop losing sleep over?","goodResponse":"That peace of mind is the real deliverable. Let me show you how other contractors your size have made that transition.","badResponse":"We integrate all of that. Let's schedule a demo.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"Do you have a dedicated IT setup for your office, or is it mostly consumer-grade equipment that someone set up when you first started?","goodResponse":"A lot of trades businesses reach a point where the original setup is holding growth back. It helps me understand what the foundation looks like before talking about what you need.","badResponse":"We upgrade those setups all the time.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"How often do your estimators or office staff deal with slow computers, printer issues, or software crashes that kill their momentum during a busy quoting period?","goodResponse":"That friction is invisible in the budget but very visible in turnaround time and staff frustration. What's the worst recurring issue you deal with?","badResponse":"We tune up office equipment and eliminate those slowdowns.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a slow system causes your estimator to miss a bid submission window or delay a quote by a day, how often does that translate directly to lost work?","goodResponse":"In a competitive bid environment, a day can be the difference between landing the job and losing it. That's a direct revenue consequence of infrastructure that isn't keeping up.","badResponse":"Delays lose bids. We speed things up.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your office ran on fast, reliable, managed hardware and software — with someone to call when something goes wrong — what would that do for your estimating and admin capacity?","goodResponse":"That reliability compounds over time. Let me put together what a managed IT baseline looks like for a contractor your size.","badResponse":"We provide that baseline. Let's talk.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}]],"auto_services":[[{"phase":"situation","question":"How are you managing your DMS — dealer management system or shop management software — is that cloud-hosted or running on local servers in the building?","goodResponse":"Local DMS servers are often the most neglected piece of infrastructure in auto businesses. That tells me something about your backup situation and your vulnerability window.","badResponse":"We support all the major DMS platforms.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Have you ever had your DMS or parts lookup system go down during a busy service day — and had to write repair orders by hand or tell customers to wait?","goodResponse":"That's a service throughput problem that affects your daily revenue and your team's ability to close jobs. How long did it take to recover, and who ended up fixing it?","badResponse":"DMS downtime is a real problem. We prevent it.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If your service lane goes down for two hours on a Saturday morning, how many jobs does that cost you — and what does the customer ripple effect look like for your appointments that week?","goodResponse":"The revenue impact is immediate, but the scheduling disruption cascades for days. That's exactly the kind of event that a proactive monitoring setup eliminates.","badResponse":"It adds up fast. We keep those systems running.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your DMS, parts systems, and service bay computers were all monitored and maintained proactively — with guaranteed response times — how would that change how you manage your service department?","goodResponse":"That reliability is what your service manager and your CSI scores both depend on. Let me walk you through what that managed setup looks like.","badResponse":"We provide that managed service. Let's scope it out.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"How are your salespeople accessing inventory, financing tools, and customer records — are they working off one platform, or is it spread across multiple systems?","goodResponse":"Sales floor fragmentation is one of the biggest productivity drains I see in dealerships. What does the average salesperson's screen workflow look like when they're working a deal?","badResponse":"We integrate dealership systems to streamline the sales floor.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Do your salespeople ever lose momentum in a deal because they're waiting for a system to load, re-entering the same customer data in multiple places, or chasing down approval from someone who has access they don't?","goodResponse":"Every friction point in that process is a moment where a customer reconsiders. What does the worst version of that experience look like from your floor?","badResponse":"We streamline those workflows to keep deals moving.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a deal takes 30 minutes longer than it needs to because of system friction, and that leads to one fewer closed deal per week — what does that add up to over a quarter?","goodResponse":"At your average gross per unit, that's a meaningful number. And the frustration on the salesperson's side affects retention too.","badResponse":"Lost time means lost deals. We fix that.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your sales team had fast, integrated tools where customer data flowed from lead to F&I without re-entry — what would that do for your close rate and your CSI?","goodResponse":"That's the environment high-performing dealerships run. Let me show you what an integrated sales floor IT setup looks like for a store your size.","badResponse":"We build that integration. Ready to talk specs?","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"Do you have security cameras and access control at your lot — and are those systems managed centrally or are they separate installs that no one's really touched since setup?","goodResponse":"Lot security and access control are often set-and-forget systems that eventually become liabilities. What does oversight of those systems look like right now?","badResponse":"We manage and modernize security infrastructure for auto businesses.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Have you had a lot theft, a vehicle move dispute, or a security incident where the camera footage wasn't clear enough or wasn't accessible when you needed it?","goodResponse":"That gap between having cameras and having usable footage is where a lot of claims fall apart. What did that situation cost you?","badResponse":"We ensure your cameras are actually usable when it matters.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a vehicle theft or damage claim can't be resolved because your footage is too grainy or gets overwritten before you pull it — what does that mean for your insurance claim and your deductible exposure?","goodResponse":"That's a direct out-of-pocket cost that good footage would have covered. The ROI on a properly managed camera system pays for itself on the first saved claim.","badResponse":"Good footage saves money on claims. We make sure you have it.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your lot cameras, access controls, and alarm systems were all managed, monitored, and accessible from your phone in real time — how much more confident would you feel about what's happening on your property after hours?","goodResponse":"That confidence is the deliverable. Let me walk you through what a managed security infrastructure package looks like for a dealership or shop your size.","badResponse":"We provide exactly that. Let's put a proposal together.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}]],"financial_services":[[{"phase":"situation","question":"Are your advisors and staff accessing client portfolio data and CRM from a centrally managed environment, or are people using their own devices and methods?","goodResponse":"That's a common setup in boutique firms, but it creates real challenges around data governance and audit trails. Tell me more about how access is controlled today.","badResponse":"We standardize and secure those environments.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Have you had any incidents where a client record was accessed by someone who shouldn't have had visibility into it — even a benign mix-up between advisors?","goodResponse":"Even an innocent access event can become a regulatory issue under Reg S-P if it touches client financial data. How are you currently auditing who looks at what?","badResponse":"Access control is critical for financial firms. We handle it.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a regulatory exam found gaps in your access control logs or your data handling procedures — what does a deficiency finding look like for your firm and your registered principals?","goodResponse":"A deficiency finding doesn't just cost you in the exam cycle — it becomes a flag that follows your firm into future exams. The documentation and controls work is much easier done proactively.","badResponse":"Regulatory findings are serious. We get you compliant.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If you had a managed IT environment where every access event was logged, every device was policy-compliant, and you could generate an audit-ready report on demand — how would that change your exam prep process?","goodResponse":"Firms that have that infrastructure in place treat exam prep as a non-event. That's exactly the outcome we build toward. Let me show you what that looks like.","badResponse":"We provide exam-ready IT compliance. Let's talk.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"How are your advisors handling client communications — email, texting, voice — and are all of those channels being archived the way your compliance program requires?","goodResponse":"Communication archiving is one of the most consistently cited deficiencies in FINRA exams. What does your current archiving solution look like, and who owns it?","badResponse":"We provide compliant communication archiving for financial firms.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Has a client ever communicated something important through an unarchived channel — a text, a personal email — that later became part of a dispute or suitability question?","goodResponse":"That's a scenario where missing records hurt you even when you did everything right. What does your current visibility into advisor-client communication actually look like?","badResponse":"We make sure every channel is captured and archived.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a FINRA arbitration surfaced a client complaint and you couldn't produce records of a communication that happened through an unmonitored channel — how does that affect your firm's defense and your E&O exposure?","goodResponse":"That's the worst position to be in — defending a claim without the records you should have. The firms that archive everything have a fundamentally different risk profile.","badResponse":"Missing records hurt in disputes. We make sure you have them.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If every advisor communication — email, text, voice — was automatically archived, searchable, and supervision-ready from day one, how much simpler does your compliance oversight become?","goodResponse":"That's the compliance environment forward-thinking firms are building. Let me walk you through how that unified archiving solution works.","badResponse":"We build that for you. Let's schedule a demo.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"When a new advisor joins your firm, how long does it take to get them fully provisioned — systems access, email, CRM, archiving, compliance tools — before they're operational?","goodResponse":"Onboarding latency in financial services has a direct revenue cost — advisors who can't access their book of business are generating zero AUM. What does that window typically look like for you?","badResponse":"We streamline advisor onboarding for financial firms.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Have you had advisors frustrated during their first weeks because systems weren't ready, logins weren't working, or access to client data was delayed by IT issues?","goodResponse":"First impressions matter for retention. If an advisor joins and immediately hits friction, that shapes their perception of the firm. What does that friction typically look like?","badResponse":"We eliminate that onboarding friction.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a newly recruited advisor is unproductive for two weeks due to IT delays, and they came with a meaningful book — what does that lag cost in foregone revenue and in their confidence about the move they made?","goodResponse":"That confidence hit is harder to measure than the revenue loss, but it's often more consequential for retention. Getting that setup right the first time sends a strong signal.","badResponse":"Delays cost money and morale. We fix that.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If we could guarantee that any new advisor is fully provisioned and operational on their first day — every system, every compliance tool, every access credential ready to go — how would that change your recruiting pitch?","goodResponse":"That's a real differentiator when you're recruiting experienced advisors who know what good looks like. Let me show you our onboarding playbook.","badResponse":"We make day-one readiness a guarantee. Let's talk.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}]],"real_estate":[[{"phase":"situation","question":"How are your agents accessing the MLS, transaction management platform, and client CRM — are those all cloud-based, or do you have any local server infrastructure?","goodResponse":"Real estate offices are often running a mix of cloud tools with some legacy local infrastructure underneath. That tells me where the reliability and security gaps usually live.","badResponse":"We support real estate technology stacks of all types.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Have your agents ever had trouble accessing transaction documents, e-signature platforms, or the MLS during a critical window — like right before a contract deadline?","goodResponse":"In real estate, a 30-minute connectivity problem at the wrong moment can cost a client their deal. How often does something like that happen, and what's the fallback when it does?","badResponse":"We prevent those connectivity failures.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If an agent misses a counter-offer deadline because their system was down or their VPN dropped — what does that do to the client relationship and the firm's reputation in a competitive market?","goodResponse":"That's the kind of story that becomes a Yelp review and a word-of-mouth warning. One missed deadline can undo months of relationship building.","badResponse":"Reliability protects your reputation. We provide it.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If every agent had a guaranteed-reliable, secure remote work setup with zero-downtime access to every platform they use — what does that do for agent productivity and client confidence in your brand?","goodResponse":"That reliability becomes a recruiting tool and a retention tool at the same time. Let me walk you through what that managed setup looks like for a brokerage your size.","badResponse":"We provide that. Let's put a proposal together.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"How are you handling cybersecurity for your office — do you have any endpoint protection, email filtering, or is it mostly relying on whatever comes with your devices?","goodResponse":"Real estate transactions involve wire transfers and title information, which makes the industry a consistent phishing target. I want to understand what your current defense posture looks like.","badResponse":"We provide cybersecurity for real estate offices.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"Has anyone at your firm ever received a phishing email that looked like it came from a title company, escrow agent, or even another agent — asking to change wire instructions?","goodResponse":"Wire fraud via phishing is the number-one financial crime targeting real estate right now. Even one convincing email to a client or agent can redirect a closing wire permanently.","badResponse":"Wire fraud phishing is rampant in real estate. We protect against it.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a client wired their down payment to a fraudulent account because of a compromised email in your transaction chain — what is the firm's liability exposure and what does that do to your E&O coverage?","goodResponse":"That scenario plays out multiple times a week in brokerages across the country. The firms that have layered email security are the ones that can say it's never happened to them.","badResponse":"The liability is serious. We build the protection layers.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If your email environment had multi-factor authentication, advanced phishing detection, and wire fraud warning protocols built in — how much safer would your clients' transactions be?","goodResponse":"That security posture becomes a competitive differentiator — clients choose brokerages they trust with their largest financial transaction. Let me show you what that stack looks like.","badResponse":"We build that. It's not complicated. Let's talk.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}],[{"phase":"situation","question":"Do you have a standardized technology setup across your agents, or does everyone kind of pick their own tools and devices?","goodResponse":"BYOD environments in real estate create real challenges around data security and compliance. It tells me that your firm's data may be spread across personal devices without consistent protection.","badResponse":"We standardize and secure agent device environments.","rapportOnGood":1,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"situation_questions","framework":"SPIN – Situation"},{"phase":"problem","question":"When an agent leaves your brokerage, how confident are you that all the client data, transaction records, and contacts they had on their personal device are actually gone and not walking out with them?","goodResponse":"That's a gap most brokerages don't think about until a departed agent pops up at a competitor with a suspiciously familiar client list. What does your offboarding process look like today?","badResponse":"We handle offboarding and data security for agent transitions.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"problem_questions","framework":"SPIN – Problem"},{"phase":"implication","question":"If a former agent retained your client database and used it at a competing brokerage, what does that mean for your pipeline — and do you have the documentation to pursue any recourse?","goodResponse":"Without documentation of device use and data access, recourse is nearly impossible. It's a gap that's very expensive to discover after the fact.","badResponse":"Data loss from departing agents is a real problem. We prevent it.","rapportOnGood":2,"rapportOnBad":-1,"skillTag":"implication_questions","framework":"SPIN – Implication"},{"phase":"need_payoff","question":"If every agent's device was managed, their data access was logged, and an offboarding checklist automatically wiped firm data when they left — how would that change your confidence in protecting your client relationships?","goodResponse":"That's the kind of infrastructure that protects the brokerage's biggest asset — its client relationships. Let me walk you through how we've built this for other firms your size.","badResponse":"We provide that MDM solution. Let's scope it out.","rapportOnGood":3,"rapportOnBad":0,"skillTag":"need_payoff","framework":"SPIN – Need-Payoff"}]]};
